*La conférence à ne pas manquer : GeoFARMatics 2010
*24-26 novembre - COLOGNE
Information exchange in agricultural production has become a crucial 
factor for socio-economic and environmental objectives. Recent 
developments in the field of geo-technology have boosted this topic. 
Many efforts have already been made, but still there are huge 
challenges. Join GeoFARMatics, held from 24-26 November 2010 in Köln, 
Germany, the event for Geo-Information and Information Management for 
Future Farms, Agri-Food business and Administration and meet the challenge.

Why should you attend GeoFARMatics 2010?
- To share knowledge between industry (agricultural software companies, 
machine manufactures, system developers), science (researchers, 
students) and governments (advisors, policy makers, administrators) to 
learn from each other;
- To discuss the impact of geo-information in implementing agricultural 
policy and discover how to stimulate information exchanges in agriculture;
- To exchange experiences with procedures, methods, tools, standards to 
support information exchange between software products, platforms and 
other devices (machinery, office-PC, internet, etc.);
- And to give your voice in the "Cologne-declaration on Information 
Exchange and ICT in European Agriculture".

If you think your opinion matters, join in and discuss with leading 
experts in the fields of subject. Don't hesitate, as the entrance fee is 
low and the gains are high! Sign in today through www.geoFARMatics.org. 
Names of GeoFARMatics' keynote speakers are to be confirmed soon, so 
keep an eye on our website. As a subscriber you will receive the yellow 
paper of the "Cologne-declaration on ICT in the European Agriculture" on 
beforehand. Every participant will get the chance to respond during the 
declaration session and contribute to the resulting final version.

GeoFARMatics is a key, three-day conference focusing on the use of 
geo-information to support agriculture and the related value added chain 
of production. Alongside GeoFARMatics there is an associated 
international exhibition from system and component manufacturers of 
software and hardware, logistics and service companies. With its focus 
on trends in ICT technology and applications GeoFARMatics addresses the 
technology advances in agriculture, and the challenges and 
opportunities, which face service providers in applying solutions to 
agribusinesses.

GeoFARMatics provides an appealing program, varying from traditional 
elements like keynotes, from prominent and internationally renowned 
speakers in the fields of EU-policy, machine manufacturers & 
geo-information, to innovative elements like a 'Pecha Kucha' 
presentation series. Separate paper sessions, workshops and poster 
sessions address more specific topics, alternated with exhibition- and 
demonstration breaks, an icebreaker and a networking dinner.

The scientific topics that will be addressed are: Farm Management 
Information Systems; Designing international standards for information 
exchange in agribusiness; Standardisation and Interoperability; 
Providing standards through Web Services; Trends in Geo Information for 
farmers and administration; Trends for ICT in agribusiness; Emerging 
technologies in Ag-Software; Emerging technologies in on-farm 
geo-information applications & software.

GeoFARMatics is organised by The EU-funded projects FutureFarm 
(www.futurefarm.eu <http://www.futurefarm.eu/>) and agriXchange 
(www.agrixchange.eu <http://www.agrixchange.eu/>) as well as the 
CAPIGI-network (www.capigi.eu <http://www.capigi.eu/>). For further 
information on the subjects of discussion, the venue and your conference 
subscription please visit http://www.geoFARMatics2010.org 
<http://www.geofarmatics2010.org/> and do it today, as the number of 
participants is limited to keep the discussion vibrant.


