*Thought for today
*While fame impedes and constricts, obscurity wraps about a man like a 
mist; obscurity is dark, ample, and free; obscurity lets the mind take 
its way unimpeded. Over the obscure man is poured the merciful suffusion 
of darkness. None knows where he goes or comes. He may seek the truth 
and speak it; he alone is free; he alone is truthful, he alone is at 
peace. - Virginia WOOLF, writer (1882-1941)


