                              <b>La conf&eacute;rence &agrave; ne pas manquer :
                                GeoFARMatics 2010 <br>
                              </b>24-26 novembre - COLOGNE<br>
                              Information exchange in agricultural
                              production has become a crucial factor for
                              socio-economic and environmental
                              objectives. Recent developments in the
                              field of geo-technology have boosted this
                              topic. Many efforts have already been
                              made, but still there are huge challenges.
                              Join GeoFARMatics, held from 24-26
                              November 2010 in K&ouml;ln, Germany, the event
                              for Geo-Information and Information
                              Management for Future Farms, Agri-Food
                              business and Administration and meet the
                              challenge.<br>
                              <br>
                              Why should you attend GeoFARMatics 2010?<br>
                              - To share knowledge between industry
                              (agricultural software companies, machine
                              manufactures, system developers), science
                              (researchers, students) and governments
                              (advisors, policy makers, administrators)
                              to learn from each other; <br>
                              - To discuss the impact of geo-information
                              in implementing agricultural policy and
                              discover how to stimulate information
                              exchanges in agriculture;<br>
                              - To exchange experiences with procedures,
                              methods, tools, standards to support
                              information exchange between software
                              products, platforms and other devices
                              (machinery, office-PC, internet, etc.);<br>
                              - And to give your voice in the
                              &#8220;Cologne-declaration on Information
                              Exchange and ICT in European Agriculture&#8221;.<br>
                              <br>
                              If you think your opinion matters, join in
                              and discuss with leading experts in the
                              fields of subject. Don&#8217;t hesitate, as the
                              entrance fee is low and the gains are
                              high! Sign in today through
                              <a class="moz-txt-link-abbreviated" href="http://www.geoFARMatics.org">www.geoFARMatics.org</a>. Names of
                              GeoFARMatics&#8217; keynote speakers are to be
                              confirmed soon, so keep an eye on our
                              website. As a subscriber you will receive
                              the yellow paper of the
                              &#8220;Cologne-declaration on ICT in the
                              European Agriculture&#8221; on beforehand. Every
                              participant will get the chance to respond
                              during the declaration session and
                              contribute to the resulting final version.<br>
                              <br>
                              GeoFARMatics is a key, three-day
                              conference focusing on the use of
                              geo-information to support agriculture and
                              the related value added chain of
                              production. Alongside GeoFARMatics there
                              is an associated international exhibition
                              from system and component manufacturers of
                              software and hardware, logistics and
                              service companies. With its focus on
                              trends in ICT technology and applications
                              GeoFARMatics addresses the technology
                              advances in agriculture, and the
                              challenges and opportunities, which face
                              service providers in applying solutions to
                              agribusinesses.<br>
                              <br>
                              GeoFARMatics provides an appealing
                              program, varying from traditional elements
                              like keynotes, from prominent and
                              internationally renowned speakers in the
                              fields of EU-policy, machine manufacturers
                              &amp; geo-information, to innovative
                              elements like a &#8216;Pecha Kucha&#8217; presentation
                              series. Separate paper sessions, workshops
                              and poster sessions address more specific
                              topics, alternated with exhibition- and
                              demonstration breaks, an icebreaker and a
                              networking dinner. <br>
                              <br>
                              The scientific topics that will be
                              addressed are: Farm Management Information
                              Systems; Designing international standards
                              for information exchange in agribusiness;
                              Standardisation and Interoperability;
                              Providing standards through Web Services;
                              Trends in Geo Information for farmers and
                              administration; Trends for ICT in
                              agribusiness; Emerging technologies in
                              Ag-Software; Emerging technologies in
                              on-farm geo-information applications &amp;
                              software. <br>
                              <br>
                              GeoFARMatics is organised by The EU-funded
                              projects FutureFarm (<a
                                href="http://www.futurefarm.eu/">www.futurefarm.eu</a>)
                              and agriXchange (<a
                                href="http://www.agrixchange.eu/">www.agrixchange.eu</a>)
                              as well as the CAPIGI-network (<a
                                href="http://www.capigi.eu/">www.capigi.eu</a>).
                              For further information on the subjects of
                              discussion, the venue and your conference
                              subscription please visit <a
                                href="http://www.geofarmatics2010.org/">http://www.geoFARMatics2010.org</a>
                              and do it today, as the number of
                              participants is limited to keep the
                              discussion vibrant.</font><br>
